          "Sign Up Log In Purchase a Subscription Shumaker Advisors announced Tuesday that Sanford would be joining the firm as an executive vice president and principal.",
          "He has a command of the issues, the process, and the politics, and our clients will be well served by his leadership,” said Shumaker Advisors Florida executive vice president David Jolly, a former congressman whose time in the House overlapped with Sanford's second congressional career.",
